07/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Military officials announced on Thursday (August 6th) that the army has resumed raids along the border with northern Iraq and have bombed the town of Cukurca.
No injuries were reported.
Separately Thursday, CNN Turk reported that one person in Uludere was killed by a bomb allegedly planted by the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party.
(UPI, Kuna, CNN - 06/08/09)
